@JLLeitschuh We'd like to get 5.1 M1 out the door as soon as possible (perhaps as early as tonight).

So, with that in mind, if you could implement the necessary changes for Kotlin ASAP, that'd be awesome!

FYI: I think I'll be pushing the necessary changes on the Java side within the next few minutes. :wink:

@sbrannen 

> Never mind... `Iterable<Executable>` doesn't even work in Java since it _clashes_ with `Executable...` which is an array which is also an `Iterable`.

Oh, really? I knew that arrays could be subjects for foreach loops, but I believe that this code example is actually illegal?

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
  iterateAndPrint(args);
}

private static void iterateAndPrint(Iterable<String> values) {
  values.forEach(System.out::println);
}
```

I'm sure I've misunderstood something here. Would you mind clarifying things further for me?
